      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ICE AGE (4) is a talented type with an excellent strike rate at this journey. Jumped well when winning his last couple. Last start won Murray Bridge in a handy 22.35 beating Canya Nameless. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. The hardest to beat again. DANYO'S ALBIE (5) has a strong record this trip with eight wins and nine placings from 22 starts. Placed last time (17.21) at Murray Bridge in a Grade 5, finishing third and beaten 5.5 lengths. Can feature with the right run. JABUK (1) is a promising type who notched his 16th career success when too good (23.34) at Horsham last time. Solid record here at the distance winning seven races. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Hard to fault his form and makes plenty of appeal again. PET DETECTIVE (8) is last start winner who looks one of the chances.",
